commit.message: Adapt README and changelog to 4.13 support

Simplify last simplifiable migration function

The functions `copy_location` and `copy_Longident_t` have already been
simplified. Those two together with `copy_location_stack` are the only
functions whose signature doesn't rely on AST types.

ocp-indent: Forbid ocp-ident to take the system preset to indent comments

Apparently the current behaviour of ocp-indent is such that if no preset is given, it will fallback to the system preset (e.g. from ~/.ocp/ocp-indent.conf). This simplifies porting ocaml-migrate-parsetree to a new version of OCaml quite a bit.
Update to the latest magic number
Simplify some simplifiable migration functions
Restore compatibility with older OCaml version

[3/3] Enable OCaml 4.13 in cinaps and opam

Co-authored-by: Sonja Heinze <sonjaleaheinze@gmail.com>

[2/3] Fix the generated migration functions and add missing cases

Co-authored-by: Sonja Heinze <sonjaleaheinze@gmail.com>

[1/3] Add support for OCaml 4.13: completed Ast_413.ml, unmodified generated migrate_* files

Co-authored-by: Sonja Heinze <sonjaleaheinze@gmail.com>
